  "summaries": [
    "The <b>Healing Potion</b> is a <linked>recovery potion</linked> that restores 100 <linked>health</linked> and inflicts <linked>Potion Sickness</linked> for 60 seconds when used. This duration can be reduced via the <linked>Philosopher's Stone</linked> or <linked>Charm of Myths</linked>.",
    "In addition to being crafted, Healing Potions can be found naturally in <linked>pots</linked> after <linked>Hardmode</linked> activation and pots in the <linked>Underworld</linked> in <linked>pre-Hardmode</linked>. Healing Potions also dropped from <span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Deerclops</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span></span>, <linked>Skeletron</linked>, and the <linked>Wall of Flesh</linked>, <span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span> and are sold by the <linked>Merchant</linked> and the <linked>Skeleton Merchant</linked> in Hardmode for <span class=\"coin\" title=\"10 Silver Coins\" data-sort-value=\"1000\"><span class=\"sc\">10<i> SC</i></span></span>.",
    "It is the second tier of healing potion, succeeding the <linked>Lesser Healing Potion</linked>, and preceding the <linked>Greater Healing Potion</linked> and <span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Super Healing Potion</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span></span>."
